[thinking: Now I can see the issue! In line 542-553, when `isInMultiSelectMode` is true and a row is clicked:

```kotlin
cardsListView.setOnItemClickListener { _: AdapterView<*>?, view: View?, position: Int, _: ...]
Now I can see the bug! Looking at line 542-553:

1. When clicking on a row in multi-select mode, the code calls:
   - `cb.toggle()` - toggles the checkbox visually
   - `viewModel.selectRowAtPosition(position)` - only **adds** to selection, never removes

2. But when clicking directly on the checkbox (line 1837), it correctly calls:
   - `viewModel.toggleRowSelectionAtPosition(position)` - properly toggles selection (add/remove)

The `selectRowAtPosition` function in the ViewModel only adds cards to selection:
```kotlin
fun selectRowAtPosition(pos: Int) {
    if (_selectedRows.add(cards[pos])) {  // Only adds, never removes
        refreshSelectedRowsFlow()
    }
}
```

While `toggleRowSelectionAtPosition` properly handles both adding and removing:
```kotlin
fun toggleRowSelectionAtPosition(position: Int) {
    val card = cards[position]
    if (_selectedRows.contains(card)) {
        _selectedRows.remove(card)
    } else {
        _selectedRows.add(card)
    }
    refreshSelectedRowsFlow()
